 class=\"fn\">Γ</span> <span class=\"fn\">Λ</span> <span class=\"fn\">σ</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Computability/PostTuringMachine.html#Turing.TM1.Stmt.write","kind":"ctor","line":316,"name":"Turing.TM1.Stmt.write","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Computability/PostTuringMachine.lean#L316-L316"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Computability/PostTuringMachine.html#Turing.TM1.Stmt.move\"><span class=\"name\">Turing</span>.<span class=\"name\">TM1</span>.<span class=\"name\">Stmt</span>.<span class=\"name\">move</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Γ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Λ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">σ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Computability/Tape.html#Turing.Dir\">Dir</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Computability/PostTuringMachine.html#Turing.TM1.Stmt\">Stmt</a> <span class=\"fn\">Γ</span> <span class=\"fn\">Λ</span> <span class=\"fn\">σ</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Computability/PostTuringMachine.html#Turing.TM1.Stmt\">Stmt</a> <span class=\"fn\">Γ</span> <span class=\"fn\">Λ</span> <span class=\"fn\">σ</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Computability/PostTuringMachine.html#Turing.TM1.Stmt.move","kind":"ctor","line":315,"name":"Turing.TM1.Stmt.move","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Computability/PostTuringMachine.lean#L315-L315"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">inductive</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Computability/PostTuringMachine.html#Turing.TM1.Stmt\"><span class=\"name\">Turing</span>.<span class=\"name\">TM1</span>.<span class=\"name\">Stmt</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">Γ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">Λ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">σ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max (max u_1 u_2) u_3)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"The TM1 model is a simplification and extension of TM0\n(Post-Turing model) in the direction of Wang B-machines. The machine's\ninternal state is extended with a (finite) store `σ` of variables\nthat may be accessed and updated at any time.\nA machine is given by a `Λ` indexed set of procedures or functions.\nEach function has a body which is a `Stmt`, which can either be a\n`move` or `write` command, a `branch` (if statement based on the\ncurrent tape value), a `load` (set the variable value),\na `goto` (call another function), or `halt`. Note that here\nmost statements do not have labels; `goto` commands can only\ngo to a new function. All commands have access to the variable value\nand current tape value. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Computability/PostTuringMachine.html#Turing.TM1.Stmt","kind":"inductive","line":302,"name":"Turing.TM1.Stmt","sourceLink":"http